ZH: 请你听话，不要在教室里说话。
EN: Please listen and be quiet in the classroom.

ZH: 他是个听话的孩子，从来不会给父母添麻烦。
EN: He is a well-behaved child who never causes trouble for his parents.

ZH: 我们的狗非常听话，从不乱叫。
EN: Our dog is very obedient and never barks uncontrollably.

ZH: 她虽然听话，但有时也会有自己的想法。
EN: Although she is obedient, she sometimes has her own opinions.

ZH: 坐下，好好听话，别再闹了。
EN: Sit down, listen carefully, and stop causing trouble.

ZH: 我们需要的是一个能听话的员工，而不是一个想当老板的人。
EN: What we need is an employee who listens and obeys, not someone who wants to be the boss.

ZH: 这位老人非常听话，总是按时吃药。
EN: This elderly person is very obedient and always takes medication on time.

ZH: 只有听话的学生才能得到老师的赞扬。
EN: Only obedient students will receive praise from the teacher.

ZH: 她一直以来都是个听话的姑娘，从不违抗父母的意愿。
EN: She has always been an obedient girl who never disobeys her parents.

ZH: 请你听话，不要在公共场合大声喧哗。
EN: Please be obedient and do not make a loud noise in public places.

ZH: 如果你不听话，我就要惩罚你了。
EN: If you don't listen, I will have to punish you.

ZH: 要成为一个优秀的领导者，首先要学会听话。
EN: To be an excellent leader, you must first learn to listen and obey.

ZH: 只有听话的乘客才能留在车厢内。
EN: Only obedient passengers are allowed to stay in the carriage.

ZH: 如果你听话，我保证会奖励你。
EN: If you obey, I promise to reward you.

ZH: 要做一名成功的商人，首先必须懂得听话。
EN: To be a successful businessman, one must first understand the importance of listening and obeying.

ZH: 只有听话的员工才能获得升职的机会。
EN: Only obedient employees have the opportunity to be promoted.

ZH: 他一直都是个很听话的男孩，从不给任何人添麻烦。
EN: He has always been a very obedient boy who never causes trouble for anyone.

ZH: 只有听话的学生才有资格参加这次活动。
EN: Only obedient students are eligible to participate in this event.

ZH: 如果你再不听话，我就要生气了。
EN: If you still don't listen, I will get angry.

ZH: 要成为一个好老师，必须懂得如何让学生听话。
EN: To be a good teacher, one must know how to make students listen and obey. 
